    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWithin the plugin ecosystem, `q` (in normal mode) is a common mapping to close floating windows. It's also used within core, to close the LSP Hover window.\n\nUsually, floating windows aren't modifiable, so having `q` mapped to recording a macro isn't all that useful.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`q` should be mapped to `:quit` for floats.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Why would it only be for floats? We could consider a default `q` mapping to do this. But that (or even the \"floats only\" case) is blocked until we think of a good way to opt-in to the normal purpose of `q` (start a macro).",
